svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-feedback\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-feedback\"></use></svg><span class=\"zDocsFeedbackButtonText\"> Feedback</span></span></div></div><div class=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><button aria-label=\"Show topic actions\" data-toggle=\"dropdown\" id=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-ellipsis-h\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-ellipsis-h\"></use></svg></button><div class=\"dropdown-menu zDocsDropdownMenu zDocsTopicActionsMobileDropdown dropdown-menu-right\"></div></div><div style=\"flex-basis: 100%; height: 0px;\"></div><ul class=\"zDocsTopicPageDetails\"><li class=\"zDocsTopicPageDate css-cinqea\">Last Updated<span class=\"css-cinqea\">Sept 20, 2024</span></li><li class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryDetailsItem\"><button class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryButton\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-topic-summary\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-topic-summary\"></use></svg>Summarize</button></li><li class=\"spacer\" role=\"presentation\"></li><div class=\"zDocsLabelWrapper\"><ul><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: Uniface\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=prod_uniface\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>Uniface</a></li><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: 10.4\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=uniface_10.4\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>10.4</a></li></ul></div></ul></header><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBody\" data-prismjs-copy=\"Copy\" data-prismjs-copy-error=\"Copy failed! Use Ctrl + C instead.\" data-prismjs-copy-success=\"Copied!\"><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBodyContent\" dir=\"ltr\"><div id=\"zDocsAiSummaryContaineruniface_104hwq1665702797151.html\"></div><div><article class=\"hascomments\" data-page=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/hwq1665702797151.html\" id=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/hwq1665702797151.html\"><main role=\"main\"><article aria-labelledby=\"ariaid-title1\" class=\"dita\" id=\"hwq1665702797151\" role=\"article\">\n<h1 class=\"title topictitle1\" id=\"ariaid-title1\">\n                          \n Global Variable Library \n   </h1>\n<div class=\"body conbody\"><p class=\"shortdesc\">\n      Use this editor to define global variables that are available to all applications that use the library in which it is defined.\n </p>\n<div class=\"note note note_note\" id=\"hwq1665702797151__note_w65ab1b7b1_w66ab1b7_w67ab1\"><span class=\"note__title\">Note:</span> It is usually preferable to use component and local variables, rather than global variables.</div>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"hwq1665702797151__p_d6608e1_d6609e1_d6610e1\">Global variables are accessible to all ProcScript in an application's components, and to global ProcScripts that use the same library or the system library.</p>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"hwq1665702797151__p_d6611e1_d6612e1_d6613e1\">In a large complex application, the risk of several components overwriting the value of global variables increases. When using these variables it is important to clear them when they are no longer required.</p>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"hwq1665702797151__p_d6614e1_d6615e1_d6616e1\">Any component that uses a global variable must specify the library in which it is located. Failure to do so will generate a ProcScript compiler error.</p>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"hwq1665702797151__p_d6617e1_d6618e1_d6619e1\">Global variables of type <code class=\"ph codeph\">Handle</code> cannot be used for accessing operations. Instead, use a component handle on a service. For more information, see <a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"vni1707830115353.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/vni1707830115353.html\" title=\"A handle is a reference to an object, such as a synchronous component instance, entity, occurrence, or field. Handles can be used to call operations on the referenced object, or to pass these objects as variables and parameters.\">Handles</a>.</p>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"hwq1665702797151__section_phn_msf_5cc\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d640124e83\">Properties</h2>\n<ul class=\"ul\" id=\"hwq1665702797151__ul_b1k_nsf_5cc\">\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"hwq1665702797151__li_d3242e1_d3243e1_d3244e1\"><span class=\"ph uicontrol\">Variable</span>\n<a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"jrq1665702585385.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/jrq1665702585385.html\" title=\"Name of the development object, which uniquely identifies it.\">Name</a>\n</li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"hwq1665702797151__li_d3245e1_d3246e1_d3247e1\"><a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"xrw1665702585620.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/xrw1665702585620.html\" title=\"Use this property to briefly describe the development object in up to 256 Unicode characters.\">Description</a>\n</li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"hwq1665702797151__li_d3248e1_d3249e1_d3250e1\"><a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"aww1665702586248.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/aww1665702586248.html\" title=\"Uniface data type to use for this field, variable, or parameter. The default value is S (String).\">Data Type</a>\n</li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"hwq1665702797151__li_d3251e1_d3252e1_d3253e1\"><a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"aym1665702709149.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/aym1665702709149.html\" title=\"Interface definition for a variable or operation parameter with Data Type Handle or XMLStream.\">Classification</a>\n</li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"hwq1665702797151__li_d3254e1_d3255e1_d3256e1\"><a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"egj1665702709221.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/egj1665702709221.html\" title=\"Specify a display format for the global variable, which can be used to format the data for display or string substitution.\">Display Format (Global Variable)</a>\n</li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"hwq1665702797151__li_d3257e1_d3258e1_d3259e1\"><a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"bck1665702654827.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/bck1665702654827.html\" title=\"Extended description of the global object.\">Comments</a>\n</li>\n</ul>\n</section>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"hwq1665702797151__section_hfc_4sf_5cc\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d640124e162\">How to</h2>\n<ul class=\"ul\" id=\"hwq1665702797151__ul_n2w_4sf_5cc\">\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"hwq1665702797151__li_d3260e1_d3261e1_d3262e1\"><a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"por1705566942408.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/por1705566942408.html\" title=\"Global variables are accessible to all ProcScript in an application's components, and to global ProcScripts that use the same library or the system library.\">Working with Global Variables</a>\n</li>\n</ul>\n</section>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"hwq1665702797151__section_o5h_psf_5cc\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d640124e180\">Menu Options</h2>\n<div class=\"table-wrap\"><table class=\"table\" count-columns=\"2\" id=\"hwq1665702797151__table_d578e1_d579e1_d580e1\"><caption><span class=\"table--title-label\">Table 1. </span><span class=\"title\">Menu Options for Message Libraries</span></caption><colgroup><col/><col/></colgroup><thead class=\"thead\">\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<th class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" id=\"hwq1665702797151__table_d578e1_d579e1_d580e1__entry__1\">Menu Option </th>\n<th class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" id=\"hwq1665702797151__table_d578e1_d579e1_d580e1__entry__2\">Action </th>\n</tr>\n</thead><tbody class=\"tbody\">\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"hwq1665702797151__table_d578e1_d579e1_d580e1__entry__1\"><span class=\"ph menucascade\"><span class=\"ph uicontrol\">File &gt; Open/New</span></span>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"hwq1665702797151__table_d578e1_d579e1_d580e1__entry__2\">Open or create a new library. </td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"hwq1665702797151__table_d578e1_d579e1_d580e1__entry__1\"><span class=\"ph menucascade\"><span class=\"ph uicontrol\">File &gt; Compile</span></span>\n<p class=\"p\"><span class=\"ph menucascade\"><span class=\"ph uicontrol\">File &gt; Compile all</span></span>\n</p>\n<p class=\"p\"><span class=\"ph menucascade\"><span class=\"ph uicontrol\">File &gt; Compile modified</span></span>\n</p>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"hwq1665702797151__table_d578e1_d579e1_d580e1__entry__2\">Compile the current, all, or modified global\n                        objects. </td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"hwq1665702797151__table_d578e1_d579e1_d580e1__entry__1\"><span class=\"ph menucascade\"><span class=\"ph uicontrol\">Edit &gt; New <var class=\"keyword varname\">&lt;Global Object Type&gt; </var>\n</span></span>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"hwq1665702797151__table_d578e1_d579e1_d580e1__entry__2\">Create a new global object </td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"hwq1665702797151__table_d578e1_d579e1_d580e1__entry__1\"><span class=\"ph menucascade\"><span class=\"ph uicontrol\">Edit &gt; Duplicate <var class=\"keyword varname\">&lt;Global Object\n                                 Type&gt;</var>\n</span></span>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"hwq1665702797151__table_d578e1_d579e1_d580e1__entry__2\">Save a copy of the current global object under\n                        a different name. </td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"hwq1665702797151__table_d578e1_d579e1_d580e1__entry__1\"><span class=\"ph menucascade\"><span class=\"ph uicontrol\">Edit &gt; Delete <var class=\"keyword varname\">&lt;Global Object Type&gt;</var>\n</span></span>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"hwq1665702797151__table_d578e1_d579e1_d580e1__entry__2\">Delete the current global object. </td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"hwq1665702797151__table_d578e1_d579e1_d580e1__entry__1\"><span class=\"ph menucascade\"><span class=\"ph uicontrol\">View &gt;Zoom Field</span></span>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"hwq1665702797151__table_d578e1_d579e1_d580e1__entry__2\">Edit the selected field in a separate dialog;\n                        useful when editing text blocks and code. </td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"hwq1665702797151__table_d578e1_d579e1_d580e1__entry__1\"><span class=\"ph menucascade\"><span class=\"ph uicontrol\">View &gt;Message Frame</span></span>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"hwq1665702797151__table_d578e1_d579e1_d580e1__entry__2\">Display the message frame; useful after\n                        compiling the object.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"hwq1665702797151__table_d578e1_d579e1_d580e1__entry__1\"><span class=\"ph uicontrol\">Go To</span>\n<span class=\"ph uicontrol\">\n<var class=\"keyword varname\">&lt;Global Object Type&gt;</var>\n</span>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"hwq1665702797151__table_d578e1_d579e1_d580e1__entry__2\">Create or open a different type of global\n                        object, or library (properties).</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody></table></div>\n</section>\n</div>\n</article></main></article>\n</div></div><div class=\"contentPlaceholder\" style=\"height: 500px;\"><div class=\"contentContainer zDocsSideBoxes\"><div><h5 aria-level=\"5\" class=\"css-g931ng\">Related Links</h5><ul><li><a class=\"css-ettsdk\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/clk1665702551274.html\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-related-link\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-related-link\"></use></svg>Variables</a><p>Variables are placeholders for data whose value can change during the runtime duration of the ProcScript module, component, or application for which they have scope. The scope is determined by where they are declared.</p></li></ul></div></div></div></div><div class=\"bottomFeedback\"><div aria-labelledby=\"bottomFeedbackText\" class=\"bottomFeedbackContent\" role=\"group\"><span class=\"bottomFeedbackText\" id=\"bottomFeedbackText\">Was this topic helpful?</span><div class=\"bottomFeedbackButtonGroup\"><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_2528407\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-up\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-up\"></use></svg><span>Like</span></a><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_2528407\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-down\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-down\"></use></svg><span>Dislike</span></a></div></div></div><div style=\"position: fixed; bottom: 170px; right: 70px; cursor: pointer; transition-duration: 0.2s; transition-timing-function: linear; transition-delay: 0s; z-index: 3; opacity: 0; visibility: hidden; transition-property: opacity, visibility;\"><button aria-label=\"Scroll to top\" class=\"zDocsScrollTopBtn\" data-tooltip-content=\"Scroll to top\" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsBackToTopToolTip\" id=\"zDocsScrollToTop\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-next\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-next\"></use></svg></button></div></body></html>", "text": "Global Variable Library Add to My Topics Add selected topic and subtopics Add Topic & Subtopics with topic head Add entire publication Watch Download PDF Save selected topic Save selected topic and subtopics Save entire publication Share Email Link Copy Link Feedback Last Updated Sept 20, 2024 Summarize Uniface 10.4 Global Variable Library Use this editor to define global variables that are available to all applications that use the library in which it is defined. Note: It is usually preferable to use component and local variables, rather than global variables. Global variables are accessible to all ProcScript in an application's components, and to global ProcScripts that use the same library or the system library. In a large complex application, the risk of several components overwriting the value of global variables increases. When using these variables it is important to clear them when they are no longer required. Any component that uses a global variable must specify the library in which it is located. Failure to do so will generate a ProcScript compiler error. Global variables of type Handle cannot be used for accessing operations. Instead, use a component handle on a service. For more information, see Handles . Properties Variable Name Description Data Type Classification Display Format (Global Variable) Comments How to Working with Global Variables Menu Options Table 1. Menu Options for Message Libraries Menu Option Action File > Open/New Open or create a new library. File > Compile File > Compile all File > Compile modified Compile the current, all, or modified global objects. Edit > New <Global Object Type> Create a new global object Edit > Duplicate <Global Object Type> Save a copy of the current global object under a different name. Edit > Delete <Global Object Type> Delete the current global object. View >Zoom Field Edit the selected field in a separate dialog; useful when editing text blocks and code. View >Message Frame Display the message frame; useful after compiling the object. Go To <Global Object Type> Create or open a different type of global object, or library (properties). Related Links Variables Variables are placeholders for data whose value can change during the runtime duration of the ProcScript module, component, or application for which they have scope. The scope is determined by where they are declared. Was this topic helpful? Like Dislike"}